"The OIE's role in global efforts to combat COVID-19
------------------------------------------------------
With devastating effects on society in nearly all countries of the globe, COVID-19 has heavily challenged our food supply chains, livelihoods, economies as well as animal production systems.

The OIE has been intensively working with its network of experts and liaising closely with its members to better understand the virus and its emergence and to enhance capacity of countries to respond to this multifaceted crisis.

Read the complete document about the OIE's response to COVID-19 at https://oiebulletin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/OIE-News-May2020-Special-Edition-COVID-19-main-news-article_withoutstatement.pdf."

In this special edition of the OIE Bulletin some of the following topics are included:

- COVID-19: Our time to act on wild animal wet markets (https://oiebulletin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/OIE-News-MAY2020-Special-Edition-COVID-19-wildlife-trade-and-wet-markets_OIE-Delegates_29April2020.pdf);

- COVID-19 and the human-animal interface. In this interview, Dr Misheck Mulumba from South Africa explains the role of the OIE Expert group on COVID-19 and the human-animal interface (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4A1Y60yrhMY&feature=youtu.be);

- COVID-19 and safe trade in animals and animal products. Dr Cristobal Zepeda, OIE scientific commission president, outlines the recommendations of the OIE Expert group on COVID-19 and safe trade in animals and animal products (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EBCIY3umYXU&feature=youtu.be);

- What has the OIE been doing in response to COVID-19? An interview with OIE expert Dr William Karesh (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8i1oKOahrSQ&feature=youtu.be); and

- Dr William Karesh also discusses the importance of a One Health approach during the COVID-19 pandemic (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wP4KCixcE-c&feature=youtu.be).

